We have a utility in the code base called RandomTempFile, I think that could be a good replacement to these File.createTemptFile(..., ...) calls:

It can throw some kind of a E extends RuntimeException, which would prevent the need for us to snake this IOException through, and onto every @Test;
Instead of passing "data" every time, we could let the RandomTempFile populate some random string data.

